      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for blood viscosity (0.0035–0.004 Pa·s), power-law exponents (alpha, beta), and rotational speed. NIH sensitivity to viscosity is less than 8%; power-law exponent sensitivity is the dominant source at 14%. All within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
